ce:section.ce:para:
The DSC thermographs (Fig. 1c) indicates the crystallization and melting behaviors of the sorbent. An exothermic peak from the first cooling scan curve is seen in the temperature range of 29.89–36.17 °C which is attributed to the crystallization temperature (Tc
                        ) of the sorbent. Also, another peak is observed in the temperature range of 63.04–70.42 °C that is corresponded to the melting temperature (Tm
                        ) of the sorbent which is closely related to its crystalline structure.
